<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1020" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1020">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-15"><hi rend="italic">August 15,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bowen states that the captain of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Marietta</hi> reports no blockade at Carúpano, Caño Colorado, and
                            Guiria, and that the blockade at Ciudad Bolivar is effective. * * *)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>